quran[47]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say, 'I have been inspired that there listened a company of the ginn, and they said, \"We have heard a marvellous Qur'an"
  72,2,"that guides to the right direction; and we believe therein, and we join no one with our Lord"
  72,3,"for, verily, He - may the majesty of our Lord be exalted!- has taken to Himself neither consort nor son"
  72,4,"And, verily, a fool among us spake against God wide of the mark"
  72,5,And we thought that men and ginn would never speak a lie against God
  72,6,And there are persons amongst men who seek for refuge with persons amongst the ginn; but they increase them in their perverseness
  72,7,"And they thought, as ye thought, that God would not raise up any one from the dead"
  72,8,But we touched the heavens and found them filled with a mighty guard and shooting-stars
  72,9,and we did sit in certain seats thereof to listen; but whoso of us listens now finds a shooting-star for him on guard
  72,10,"And, verily, we know not whether evil be meant for those who are in the earth, or if their Lord means right by them"
  72,11,"And of us are some who are pious, and of us are some who are otherwise: we are in separate bands"
  72,12,"And we thought that we could not frustrate God in the earth, and could not frustrate Him by flight"
  72,13,"But, verily, when we heard the guidance we believed therein, and he who believes in his Lord shall fear neither diminution nor loss"
  72,14,"And, verily, of us are some who are Muslims, and of us some are trespassers; but those of us who are Muslims they strive after right direction"
  72,15,and as for the trespassers they are fuel for hell
  72,16,"And if they will go right upon the way, we will irrigate them with copious water"
  72,17,to try them thereby; and whoso turns from the remembrance of his Lord He will drive him to severe torment
  72,18,"And (say) that the mosques are God's, and that ye should not call on any one with God"
  72,19,and that when God's servant stood up to pray they called out to him and well-nigh crowded upon him
  72,20,"Say, 'I only call upon my Lord, and I join no one with Him"
  72,21,"Say, 'Verily, I cannot control for you either harm, or right direction"
  72,22,"Say, 'Verily, as for me none can protect me against God, nor do I find any refuge beside Him"
  72,23,"except delivering the message from God and His errands: and whoso rebels against God and His Apostle, verily, for him is the fire of hell for them to dwell therein for ever and for aye"
  72,24,"Until when they see what they are threatened with, then shall they surely know who is most weak at helping and fewest in numbers"
  72,25,"Say, 'I know not if what ye are threatened with be nigh, or if my Lord will set for it a term"
  72,26,"He knows the unseen, and He lets no one know His unseen"
  72,27,"save such apostle as He is well pleased with: for, verily, He sends marching before him and behind him a guard"
  72,28,"That He may know that they have delivered the errands of their Lord, for He compasses what they have, and reckons everything by number"
  73,1,O thou who art enwrapped
  73,2,rise by night except a little
  73,3,the half or deduct therefrom a little
  73,4,"or add thereto, and chant the Qur'an chanting"
  73,5,"Verily, we will cast on thee a heavy speech"
  73,6,"Verily, the early part of the night is stronger in impressions and more upright in speech"
  73,7,"Verily, thou hast by day a long employment"
  73,8,but mention the name of thy Lord and devote thyself thoroughly to Him
  73,9,the Lord of the east and the west; there is no god but He; then take Him for a guardian
  73,10,"And endure patiently what they say, and flee from them with a decorous flight"
  73,11,"And leave me and those who say it is a lie, who are possessed of comfort; and let them bide for a while"
  73,12,"Verily, with us are heavy fetters and hell-fire"
  73,13,"and food that chokes, and mighty woe"
  73,14,On the day when the earth and the mountains shall tremble and the earth shall be as a crumbling sand-hill
  73,15,"Verily, we have sent unto you an apostle bearing witness against you, as we sent an apostle unto Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh rebelled against the apostle, and we seized him with an overpowering punishment"
  73,17,Then how will ye shield yourselves if ye misbelieve from the day which shall make children grey-headed
  73,18,whereon the heaven cleaves - its promise shall be fulfilled
  73,19,"Verily, this is a memorial, and whoso will, let him take unto his Lord a way"